The paper discusses the use of Device-to-Device (D2D) communication in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges of relay allocation and the use of matching theory, which are topics that fall under Information Theory (cs.IT), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
